00:13:48,458 --> 00:13:51,841
[SPEAKER_03]: And we really focus on engagement.

189
00:13:52,061 --> 00:13:58,847
[SPEAKER_03]: We go to every family, where they are, and try to find out what is going to best support them and their families.

190
00:13:59,367 --> 00:14:01,108
[SPEAKER_03]: So I like to say it's a meal.

191
00:14:01,349 --> 00:14:05,011
[SPEAKER_03]: You can get your dessert first, you can get your salad first, you can get whatever you want.

192
00:14:05,031 --> 00:14:07,593
[SPEAKER_03]: It's got the full meal of programs and services.

193
00:14:07,653 --> 00:14:10,114
[SPEAKER_03]: You take what you need when you need it.

194
00:14:10,215 --> 00:14:17,299
[SPEAKER_03]: Because we don't know how your life is going to go, but we will be there for you whatever part of your life.

195
00:14:17,359 --> 00:14:20,982
[SPEAKER_03]: And as Irina said earlier, we serve families with children birth to age eight.

196
00:14:21,522 --> 00:14:25,545
[SPEAKER_03]: Well, that's great because as your children get older and you have another child,

197
00:14:26,085 --> 00:14:27,346
[SPEAKER_03]: You stay with us throughout.

198
00:14:27,746 --> 00:14:32,389
[SPEAKER_03]: We can now serve and help with an older child as we bring you on to the next child.

199
00:14:32,789 --> 00:14:34,970
[SPEAKER_03]: So we're in this family's lives long-term.

200
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:37,031
[SPEAKER_03]: It's not a short-term visit.

201
00:14:37,071 --> 00:14:38,392
[SPEAKER_03]: Unless you want it to be, of course.

202
00:14:38,432 --> 00:14:39,913
[SPEAKER_01]: No, no, I'm saying that's great.

203
00:14:40,173 --> 00:14:43,054
[SPEAKER_03]: We're there for quite a while and we listen.

204
00:14:43,574 --> 00:14:45,556
[SPEAKER_03]: I think our evolution, Irene, has been great.

205
00:14:45,576 --> 00:14:47,857
[SPEAKER_03]: We're changing how we do things.

206
00:14:48,557 --> 00:14:55,303
[SPEAKER_03]: say we'll do a six-part curriculum, and that may not quite work, so we'll do a four-part curriculum, we'll do it on Saturdays, we'll do it in the evenings.

207
00:14:55,584 --> 00:15:04,132
[SPEAKER_03]: We keep listening to our families to see how we're going to get the message of belonging and support to you in a way that you will hear it and be able to live it.

208
00:15:05,873 --> 00:15:11,695
[SPEAKER_01]: I'm just going to guess that the, you know, and I'm, but the need is probably pretty strong out there now, right?

209
00:15:11,715 --> 00:15:13,776
[SPEAKER_01]: I can only imagine.

210
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:15,617
[SPEAKER_03]: So many things have happened in COVID.

211
00:15:15,957 --> 00:15:23,140
[SPEAKER_03]: COVID is one of the things I think that has resulted in some really challenging behaviors for so many families.

212
00:15:23,621 --> 00:15:27,502
[SPEAKER_03]: So we get right in there and do as we can.

213
00:15:27,963 --> 00:15:29,883
[SPEAKER_01]: Much needed, much needed.

214
00:15:31,888 --> 00:15:38,997
[SPEAKER_01]: I know, you know, can you talk about, obviously, a lot of successes, okay?

215
00:15:39,518 --> 00:15:42,101
[SPEAKER_01]: And I'm sure there's been setbacks, too, you know?

216
00:15:43,743 --> 00:15:45,765
[SPEAKER_01]: Can you discuss some of the things you've had?

217
00:15:45,926 --> 00:15:49,670
[SPEAKER_01]: I mean, this is incredible, but, you know, some of the things that have happened.

218
00:15:52,685 --> 00:15:59,729
[SPEAKER_01]: you know, as far as success, setbacks, there's gotta be great stories, there's gotta be frustrations, I mean.

219
00:15:59,749 --> 00:16:00,209
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah.

220
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:16,259
[SPEAKER_03]: I think one of the successes, many of our successes that Irene articulated, is in our continual support for our families, but also, you know, we have been, I must say, how many awards have we received over the course of years from the state at large?

221
00:16:16,279 --> 00:16:16,439
[SPEAKER_00]: Right.

222
00:16:16,799 --> 00:16:21,542
[SPEAKER_03]: Not just the city, but from the state, recognizing the work that we've done.

223
00:16:22,442 --> 00:16:30,425
[SPEAKER_03]: Irina calculated recently the number of referrals that we had done, and we had the largest in the state of referrals, serving one city.

224
00:16:30,585 --> 00:16:32,146
[SPEAKER_03]: And we're so proud of that.

225
00:16:32,726 --> 00:16:36,067
[SPEAKER_03]: And we're proud of how we've been that way.

226
00:16:36,167 --> 00:16:43,670
[SPEAKER_03]: And I think another measure of success is how your parents then go out to the world for you and talk about it.

227
00:16:43,710 --> 00:16:47,931
[SPEAKER_03]: So they'll say, oh, Marie, Irina, I've got a new baby coming on the street.

228
00:16:48,211 --> 00:16:49,432
[SPEAKER_03]: I'm going to tell them all about the MFN.

229
00:16:50,132 --> 00:16:57,818
[SPEAKER_03]: That's a very different story from what it was three years ago when no one wanted that because it reflected badly on them, they thought.

230
00:16:58,258 --> 00:17:03,603
[SPEAKER_03]: So now, a huge success, and I'd like to say this term, is we made a cultural difference in this city.

231
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:06,285
[SPEAKER_03]: We changed this city culturally.

232
00:17:06,905 --> 00:17:09,907
[SPEAKER_03]: all for the better in a way that is for everyone.

233
00:17:10,248 --> 00:17:11,629
[SPEAKER_03]: We don't care what your politics are.

234
00:17:11,929 --> 00:17:18,434
[SPEAKER_03]: We don't care any of the other PSWs, but that you want to do the best for your family, and we'll find the way.

235
00:17:18,754 --> 00:17:19,335
[SPEAKER_03]: We'll find it.

236
00:17:19,935 --> 00:17:23,718
[SPEAKER_03]: I love to also say we have resources, referrals, and relationships.

237
00:17:24,339 --> 00:17:26,141
[SPEAKER_03]: We make the resources we can create.

238
00:17:26,601 --> 00:17:27,863
[SPEAKER_03]: We'll find the referrals.

239
00:17:27,903 --> 00:17:29,845
[SPEAKER_03]: If we can't do it, we're going to find it for you.

240
00:17:29,865 --> 00:17:30,726
[SPEAKER_03]: And we will.

241
00:17:31,267 --> 00:17:38,856
[SPEAKER_03]: And get you all the correct information, who to call, and we'll make an entree call for you so you don't feel alone by reaching out to that person.

242
00:17:39,357 --> 00:17:40,778
[SPEAKER_03]: And thirdly, relationships.

243
00:17:41,199 --> 00:17:42,280
[SPEAKER_03]: We relate to our families.

244
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:43,642
[SPEAKER_03]: We're just them to each other.

245
00:17:44,442 --> 00:17:52,424
[SPEAKER_03]: them to the cities and organizations around us, us to them, them to us, and then our organizations to each other as well.

246
00:17:53,104 --> 00:18:00,166
[SPEAKER_03]: Because we don't want to duplicate, replicate, you know, we want to fill those gaps and be meaningful in every way we can.

247
00:18:00,866 --> 00:18:03,567
[SPEAKER_03]: So I think those are major successes that we've done.

248
00:18:04,107 --> 00:18:06,788
[SPEAKER_03]: We take very serious regard of our work.

249
00:18:06,888 --> 00:18:07,288
[SPEAKER_03]: I can tell.

250
00:18:07,308 --> 00:18:08,228
[SPEAKER_03]: We have a lot of fun too.

251
00:18:08,868 --> 00:18:10,530
[SPEAKER_01]: No, you have them, that's part of it.

252
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:11,550
[SPEAKER_03]: Oh, we love them.

253
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:16,634
[SPEAKER_03]: But we take it very seriously, and so does all of our wonderful staff.

254
00:18:17,315 --> 00:18:18,315
[SPEAKER_03]: Now to the flip side.

255
00:18:19,396 --> 00:18:31,145
[SPEAKER_03]: So the setback, many of you may have heard this, but we just learned recently that one of our major funders will no longer be with us as of July 1st.

256
00:18:31,225 --> 00:18:33,647
[SPEAKER_03]: It's devastating because it's one half of our budget.

257
00:18:34,587 --> 00:18:41,792
[SPEAKER_03]: So we've been in Medford for 33 years, happily so, and we've been running this particular grant for 26 of those 33 years.

258
00:18:42,313 --> 00:18:43,473
[SPEAKER_03]: That is now gone.

259
00:18:44,814 --> 00:18:47,356
[SPEAKER_03]: And so we now have to make up for it.

260
00:18:47,396 --> 00:18:59,845
[SPEAKER_03]: So we are looking for ways to look to the city, look to the school department, look for ways to support us in that, to fulfill those positions.

261
00:19:00,925 --> 00:19:22,436
[SPEAKER_03]: That's a huge setback It doesn't stop us Right doesn't stop us, but it gives us a new affirmation and a strong as even stronger possible affirmation We need to be here and we're looking to our families have been with us to let everyone they know in the city who can help us to to tell them that

262
00:19:23,622 --> 00:19:26,966
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, no, that's tough, I know, yeah, when you lose someone like that.

263
00:19:29,208 --> 00:19:35,254
[SPEAKER_01]: So, you know, I was looking at everything, you know, next question really.

264
00:19:35,495 --> 00:19:41,461
[SPEAKER_01]: And I, you know, we understand, you know, the Friends of the Family Network, okay?

265
00:19:42,102 --> 00:19:44,044
[SPEAKER_01]: It is a funding source, right?

266
00:19:44,424 --> 00:19:44,764
[SPEAKER_01]: Okay.

267
00:19:45,505 --> 00:19:53,950
[SPEAKER_01]: So, can you tell us about them, and I'm glad you brought that up, because, you know, what about other, you know, funding sources?

268
00:19:54,050 --> 00:20:08,798
[SPEAKER_01]: I mean, it's got to be, no one likes to talk about where the money comes from, but, I mean, that's got to be important, and it's got to be a difficult task or part of the work, right, to get the funding.

269
00:20:10,088 --> 00:20:12,470
[SPEAKER_03]: So do you take this?

270
00:20:12,530 --> 00:20:12,730
[SPEAKER_03]: Sure.

271
00:20:12,870 --> 00:20:17,473
[SPEAKER_00]: Yeah, I know where, as Marie said, where we're solely grant funded and have been from day one.

272
00:20:17,613 --> 00:20:23,377
[SPEAKER_00]: OK, so losing this particular grant, which Marie mentioned, half is half of our budget.

273
00:20:23,457 --> 00:20:23,717
[SPEAKER_00]: Wow.

274
00:20:23,957 --> 00:20:27,079
[SPEAKER_00]: Is is quite quite a blow to the program.

275
00:20:27,239 --> 00:20:36,225
[SPEAKER_00]: And over the last 33 years, you know, it has grown so much with all the things that we mentioned, all the different things we're able to offer and we want to do more.

276
00:20:37,842 --> 00:20:52,170
[SPEAKER_00]: So losing that funding is making it really hard to kind of look to the future and see how we can, at this point, even sustain what we have, not even looking at growth right now, but just to sustain what we've been able to provide.

277
00:20:52,250 --> 00:21:06,358
[SPEAKER_00]: And we're open seven days a week, we're open on weekends, we're providing so many different services to so many different families that it would be quite a loss to have to look at cutting that or getting, yeah.

278
00:21:08,689 --> 00:21:17,352
[SPEAKER_00]: And sort of the nature of being grant funded is that year to year, you really don't know what the future is going to look like, right?

279
00:21:17,412 --> 00:21:18,872
[SPEAKER_00]: And so it's hard.

280
00:21:18,912 --> 00:21:26,235
[SPEAKER_00]: I mean, I know as Marie as a director, every year, you know, you're writing grants, renewing grants.

281
00:21:27,518 --> 00:21:35,325
[SPEAKER_00]: We kind of have, you know, some bigger grants that are supporting us, and so, and then there's a lot of smaller grants that we go for.

282
00:21:35,385 --> 00:21:42,231
[SPEAKER_00]: There might be for lesser amounts, but they might cover a particular program or some project that we really want to expand on.

283
00:21:42,731 --> 00:21:43,952
[SPEAKER_00]: And so we do try to

284
00:21:45,467 --> 00:21:57,219
[SPEAKER_00]: kind of expand, you know, what we're looking at and try to, you know, we work closely with Tufts University on different things and they have, you know, they have a Tufts community grant that comes out every year that we apply for every year.

285
00:21:57,239 --> 00:22:06,948
[SPEAKER_00]: Yeah, so things like that, we definitely try to leverage who we know, our partnerships, who's in the community that wants to support us and help us.

286
00:22:07,689 --> 00:22:13,171
[SPEAKER_00]: Um, you know, we've applied for things like the Cummings grant and, uh, so different, different, different sources.

287
00:22:13,271 --> 00:22:20,973
[SPEAKER_00]: And, you know, as we mentioned about having different partnerships like cradles to crayons, we work with the city of Medford, the office of prevention and outreach closely.

288
00:22:21,453 --> 00:22:35,138
[SPEAKER_00]: So, you know, there, there are ways where they're able to, to help us out when they have some funding and they're, you know, there are sometimes they've purchased toiletry items that we then give out to families during that day for plus day that I mentioned.

289
00:22:35,838 --> 00:22:35,918
[SPEAKER_00]: Um,

290
00:22:36,298 --> 00:22:43,365
[SPEAKER_00]: So we try to work really closely with our partners where we can, but those are sort of small pieces, right?

291
00:22:43,445 --> 00:22:46,968
[SPEAKER_00]: So when we lose a huge chunk like that, what we're looking for is really

292
00:22:47,858 --> 00:22:51,362
[SPEAKER_00]: It's hard to supplement that with those smaller grants.

293
00:22:51,722 --> 00:22:55,626
[SPEAKER_03]: And the Friends of the Family Network, we've done that 23 years ago.

294
00:22:55,646 --> 00:22:55,967
[SPEAKER_00]: Okay.

295
00:22:56,147 --> 00:23:01,192
[SPEAKER_03]: We've been doing it for 23, to raise the funds, so it gives us capacity.

296
00:23:01,492 --> 00:23:01,733
[SPEAKER_03]: Right.

297
00:23:01,753 --> 00:23:02,153
[SPEAKER_03]: You know what I mean?

298
00:23:02,173 --> 00:23:06,358
[SPEAKER_03]: It gives us capacity we wouldn't have otherwise because it was a grant funded program.

299
00:23:07,378 --> 00:23:11,279
[SPEAKER_03]: Other organizations like Suffolk has paid for our concerts, all of us.

300
00:23:11,479 --> 00:23:13,459
[SPEAKER_03]: So that piece was so helpful.

301
00:23:14,199 --> 00:23:18,620
[SPEAKER_03]: Gibson Southerby Realtors, they've helped us to do things, to fund different things.

302
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:20,981
[SPEAKER_03]: And as Irina said, Tufts and Cummings.

303
00:23:21,021 --> 00:23:23,901
[SPEAKER_03]: So we have that capacity to do those things as well.

304
00:23:23,981 --> 00:23:29,682
[SPEAKER_03]: And we feel confident that we use that capacity well for the smaller pieces that we have.

305
00:23:31,283 --> 00:23:32,203
[SPEAKER_03]: And yeah.

306
00:23:32,743 --> 00:23:34,524
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, and I don't think people understand.

307
00:23:34,584 --> 00:23:35,804
[SPEAKER_01]: Writing grants is not easy.

308
00:23:36,184 --> 00:23:41,947
[SPEAKER_01]: You know, applying and writing them up, it's work, right?

309
00:23:42,047 --> 00:23:46,768
[SPEAKER_01]: I mean, that's a lot of work in itself to apply for them and actually get them.

310
00:23:46,808 --> 00:23:49,749
[SPEAKER_01]: So, yeah, I know a little about that.

311
00:23:49,790 --> 00:23:52,110
[SPEAKER_01]: Not as much as you guys, but a little bit.

312
00:23:53,911 --> 00:23:59,336
[SPEAKER_01]: So, now that, you know, you said all this, so now let's get the word out.

313
00:23:59,416 --> 00:24:02,599
[SPEAKER_01]: Someone wants to help you guys out, right?

314
00:24:03,039 --> 00:24:05,121
[SPEAKER_01]: You know, I don't care how big, how small.

315
00:24:06,082 --> 00:24:07,543
[SPEAKER_01]: Someone wants to help out.

316
00:24:07,843 --> 00:24:12,287
[SPEAKER_01]: You know, how do they join the friends of the, you know, Method Filming Network?

317
00:24:12,327 --> 00:24:15,770
[SPEAKER_01]: How do they, you know, what can they do to help you, our audience?

318
00:24:17,091 --> 00:24:18,232
[SPEAKER_01]: if somebody wants to help?

319
00:24:18,272 --> 00:24:19,532
[SPEAKER_03]: That's a great question, John.

320
00:24:19,592 --> 00:24:22,034
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you very much, because there are a lot of ways that can happen.

321
00:24:22,074 --> 00:24:22,474
[SPEAKER_01]: Okay.

322
00:24:23,214 --> 00:24:24,695
[SPEAKER_03]: As Irina mentioned, donations.

323
00:24:25,135 --> 00:24:26,796
[SPEAKER_03]: You know, diapers, toiletries.

324
00:24:27,637 --> 00:24:29,658
[SPEAKER_03]: We have people coming in all the time.

325
00:24:29,718 --> 00:24:31,659
[SPEAKER_03]: We have what we call a freebie foyer.

326
00:24:31,679 --> 00:24:32,079
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay.

327
00:24:32,099 --> 00:24:40,163
[SPEAKER_03]: We have people come in every single day to select a gently used clothing of all sizes and give them back if their children have outgrown them.

328
00:24:40,243 --> 00:24:42,605
[SPEAKER_03]: So donations are always accepted.

329
00:24:43,385 --> 00:24:48,506
[SPEAKER_03]: the Friends accepts monetary donations for us and do fundraisers on our behalf all the time.

330
00:24:48,946 --> 00:24:53,528
[SPEAKER_03]: As Irina mentioned, we have an advisory board of leadership and we have friends of the Medford Family Network.

331
00:24:53,868 --> 00:25:09,972
[SPEAKER_03]: We are looking for more people who would join that wonderful group to support us, who love doing event planning, who love seeking other business partners with us and putting on galas, having some opportunities for that.

332
00:25:10,012 --> 00:25:10,532
[SPEAKER_03]: We love that.

333
00:25:11,172 --> 00:25:14,676
[SPEAKER_03]: We also have, well, we do a lot of holiday help.

334
00:25:15,617 --> 00:25:27,147
[SPEAKER_03]: We spend a lot of time in November and December sending out Thanksgiving baskets, holiday help to lots of our families in Bedford who need them.

335
00:25:27,668 --> 00:25:31,772
[SPEAKER_03]: And so those are the kinds of people who would love to step up and help us to serve those families.

336
00:25:32,372 --> 00:25:33,052
[SPEAKER_03]: and deliver them.

337
00:25:33,633 --> 00:25:34,793
[SPEAKER_03]: You know, help us deliver them.

338
00:25:34,833 --> 00:25:39,195
[SPEAKER_03]: Help us, you know, do that when families who don't have capacity to come to us.

339
00:25:39,255 --> 00:25:39,935
[SPEAKER_03]: We'll go to them.

340
00:25:40,335 --> 00:25:41,056
[SPEAKER_03]: We'll help them out.

341
00:25:41,876 --> 00:25:45,638
[SPEAKER_03]: And we have many parents who have done stepping up like that.

342
00:25:47,178 --> 00:25:52,561
[SPEAKER_01]: So you have a good group of people that are from the city of Meffitt working with you and everything else.

343
00:25:53,121 --> 00:25:58,963
[SPEAKER_01]: So in order to make it grow, that's what you're basically looking to do, right?

344
00:25:58,983 --> 00:25:59,724
[SPEAKER_01]: To get it to grow.

345
00:26:01,010 --> 00:26:07,615
[SPEAKER_01]: So if I wanted to help out, if I wanted to drop off donations, where do I go?

346
00:26:07,675 --> 00:26:09,176
[SPEAKER_01]: How do I, who do I call?

347
00:26:09,336 --> 00:26:10,236
[SPEAKER_01]: What do I do?

348
00:26:10,657 --> 00:26:12,838
[SPEAKER_03]: We have, we're called the Purple Door.

349
00:26:13,539 --> 00:26:14,659
[SPEAKER_01]: Purple Door!

350
00:26:14,739 --> 00:26:16,160
[SPEAKER_03]: We're located at Medford High School.

351
00:26:17,141 --> 00:26:22,204
[SPEAKER_03]: If anyone goes to Medford High School knows it's A105 is our number, for right now anyway.

352
00:26:23,385 --> 00:26:25,947
[SPEAKER_03]: So we are at the high school, 489 Winthrop Street.

353
00:26:26,887 --> 00:26:29,468
[SPEAKER_03]: Our number was posted there, 781-393-2106.

354
00:26:31,750 --> 00:26:34,851
[SPEAKER_03]: Call us and any of us will answer and we'll welcome you.

355
00:26:35,332 --> 00:26:36,552
[SPEAKER_03]: And we are out of our calendar.

356
