376
00:27:27,235 --> 00:27:27,775
[SPEAKER_03]: We do.

377
00:27:28,735 --> 00:27:31,296
[SPEAKER_03]: It's been a great, great support in our community.

378
00:27:31,976 --> 00:27:36,658
[SPEAKER_03]: And as we have grown over 33 years, so have other organizations in the city.

379
00:27:36,758 --> 00:27:40,899
[SPEAKER_03]: So as they grow, we grow with them.

380
00:27:41,839 --> 00:27:57,207
[SPEAKER_03]: We, as Irina mentioned, the Office of Prevention and Outreach at the City Hall, an amazing group who helps us serve our families who speak the five languages that are mainly spoken in Medford, which are Spanish, Portuguese, Haitian, Creole, Arabic, and English.

381
00:27:57,527 --> 00:28:07,892
[SPEAKER_03]: We work with those called Medford Connectors, and they help us work with those families to help us better understand them and their needs and how we can best work together with them.

382
00:28:08,752 --> 00:28:14,736
[SPEAKER_03]: We work with the Medford Housing Authority very closely with all the families there and their staff there.

383
00:28:15,356 --> 00:28:22,360
[SPEAKER_03]: We work with housing, there are many scattered sites in Medford where there are homeless families living, and you don't know that because they're living in apartments.

384
00:28:22,481 --> 00:28:24,862
[SPEAKER_03]: They're not in, and there's a shelter, heading home shelter.

385
00:28:24,902 --> 00:28:28,484
[SPEAKER_03]: We work with those seven families who are on Central Avenue, that shelter.

386
00:28:29,004 --> 00:28:31,486
[SPEAKER_03]: We're working with all the scattered site families.

387
00:28:31,506 --> 00:28:34,868
[SPEAKER_03]: We're working with all the early intervention programs.

388
00:28:35,288 --> 00:28:39,809
[SPEAKER_03]: serving children who are in speech therapy or OT or PT.

389
00:28:40,629 --> 00:28:47,831
[SPEAKER_03]: We work with all the schools, of course, our elementary schools, all the family child care providers in Medford and the homes.

390
00:28:48,291 --> 00:28:54,553
[SPEAKER_03]: We are the ones who have the updated list of all the child care centers in Medford.

391
00:28:54,673 --> 00:28:58,314
[SPEAKER_03]: Everyone needs to know that we have that list always updated.

392
00:28:59,715 --> 00:29:02,740
[SPEAKER_03]: We work with the ESOL Council.

393
00:29:02,820 --> 00:29:04,523
[SPEAKER_03]: There's an ESOL Council in Medford.

394
00:29:04,963 --> 00:29:11,073
[SPEAKER_03]: We've had English classes for the past at least 15 years for families with child care provided.

395
00:29:11,133 --> 00:29:13,176
[SPEAKER_03]: We're the only one in the city that offers

396
00:29:14,157 --> 00:29:17,702
[SPEAKER_03]: ESO classes with childcare, which is incredible.

397
00:29:17,802 --> 00:29:22,888
[SPEAKER_03]: And we have MBTA cards on occasion to get those families to us if they can't.

398
00:29:23,148 --> 00:29:24,670
[SPEAKER_03]: Or we would go to different schools.

399
00:29:25,731 --> 00:29:32,900
[SPEAKER_03]: And so we work with DCF, Department of Children and Families, where we hailed from years ago, so we get very close with them.

400
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:33,400
[SPEAKER_01]: Nice.

401
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:58,746
[SPEAKER_03]: Uh, we are together on the tilt team, T I L T, which trauma informed leadership team, leadership team in this area to really look at the, uh, trauma, look at trauma, how it affects children and families and seek programs and services that can help us to help ameliorate all that through our work individually with families and through our programs and our teamwork.

402
00:29:59,286 --> 00:30:02,687
[SPEAKER_03]: So, um, that's another place we, um, we, we focus on.

